Description: Ivory cubical die with dots carved in sunk relief.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 27
Curator's comments: "An ivory die found in chamber 27 (pl. xl. 15) and so carrying back such dice to the sixth century" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 75 § 72, pl. xl.15. Two other dice, limestone, come from Tell Dafana, probably from the Saite enclosure (so-called "Camp"), see W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 73 § 70: London UCL 59225 and Boston, MFA 87.712.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 75 § 72, pl. xl, 15)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.87, p.188, pl.30)
Condition: Broken in several fragments reunited; a few chips are missing.
